.Dd $Mdocdate: June 23 2026 $
.Dt COALESCE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm coalesce
.Nd a coalescing oneshot runner
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm run
.Ar name
.Cm --
.Ar command
.Op Ar arg ...
.Nm
.Cm trigger
.Ar name
.Nm
.Cm poke
.Ar name
.Cm --
.Ar command
.Op Ar arg ...
.Nm
.Cm status
.Ar name
.Nm
.Cm cancel
.Ar name
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
runs a command in response to external triggers.
It guarantees:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
at most one instance of the command runs at a time;
.It
triggers received while the command is running collapse into a single
pending run;
.It
on exit, the command runs once more if any trigger arrived during the run;
.It
repeated triggers never create an unbounded queue.
.El
.Pp
It manages a named, edge-triggered worker.
A trigger means:
.Dq The world may have changed; please reconcile.
The command should be written as a reconciliation task
.Pq Li sync-repo , Li deploy-latest , Li rebuild-index ,
not as a per-event handler
.Pq Li process-this-payload , Li send-one-email-per-trigger .
.Pp
The worker is a long-lived process:
.Cm run
stays alive listening on a unix socket so that command-less
.Cm trigger Ns s can reach it.
This keeps the command \(em managed by a service supervisor \(em decoupled
from the sources of triggers \(em webhooks, file watchers, timers.
.Sh SUBCOMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width "poke name -- command"
.It Cm run Ar name Cm -- Ar command Op Ar arg ...
Start the named worker loop.
The loop persists until it receives
.Dv SIGTERM
or
.Dv SIGINT ,
forwarding the signal to the running command, reaping it, and exiting.
If a worker for
.Ar name
is already running,
.Nm
exits with an error.
.It Cm trigger Ar name
Signal the worker.
If it is idle, one run is started.
If it is running, the worker is marked dirty and will run once more after the
current run finishes.
Requires a live worker
.Pq see Cm poke .
.It Cm poke Ar name Cm -- Ar command Op Ar arg ...
Ensure the worker exists, then trigger it.
If no worker is running, one is spawned detached and triggered.
If a worker is already running, only the trigger is delivered
.Pq the given command is ignored in that case .
This is the common single-command integration path for webhooks and file
watchers.
.It Cm status Ar name
Print the worker state to standard output and exit.
.It Cm cancel Ar name
Clear the pending dirty bit.
This does
.Em not
kill a currently running command.
.El
.Sh STATES
.Bl -tag -width "running dirty" -compact
.It idle
no command running; no pending run.
.It running
a command is running; no pending run.
.It running dirty
a command is running and one more run is pending.
.El
.Pp
Reported by
.Cm status ,
and as the reply to every
.Cm trigger
or
.Cm cancel .
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "XDG_RUNTIME_DIR"
.It Ev XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Base directory for the per-worker sockets.
If unset, root uses
.Pa /run
and other users use
.Pa /tmp/coalesce- Ns Em uid .
.El
.Sh FILES
Sockets live at
.Pa $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/coalesce/ Ns Em name Ns Pa .sock
.Pq or the fallback above .
The directory is created with mode
.Li 0700 .
Stale sockets left behind by a killed worker are detected and reclaimed on the
next
.Cm run
or
.Cm poke .
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width 4n -compact
.It 0
Success.
For
.Cm run ,
a clean shutdown via signal; for the others, successful delivery.
.It 1
No worker is listening
.Pq Cm trigger , Cm cancel , Cm status , or Cm poke could not reach or start a worker ,
or a worker with
.Ar name
is already running
.Pq Cm run .
.It 2
Usage error, or the managed command could not be executed
.Pq Cm run , when triggered .
.El
.Pp
The exit status of the managed command itself is not propagated:
a failed run with no pending trigger returns the worker to idle.
Retry policy is intentionally out of scope \(en use a supervisor
.Pq Xr systemd 1 , Xr cron 8 ,
or the command itself.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Ss Worker under systemd
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[Service]
Type=exec
Restart=always
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/coalesce run deploy -- /srv/app/deploy-latest
.Ed
.Ss Webhook receiver
.Bd -literal -offset indent
#!/bin/sh
coalesce trigger deploy
.Ed
.Ss Webhook receiver that also ensures the worker is up
.Bd -literal -offset indent
#!/bin/sh
coalesce poke deploy -- /srv/app/deploy-latest
.Ed
.Ss File watcher
.Bd -literal -offset indent
while inotifywait -e close_write -r src; do
    coalesce poke build -- make
done
.Ed
.Ss Introspection and cancellation
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ coalesce status deploy
running dirty
$ coalesce cancel deploy
$ coalesce status deploy
running
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr entr 1 ,
.Xr fswatch 1 ,
.Xr systemd.unit 5
.Sh AUTHORS
.An -nosplit
.An The coalesce project
.Sh CAVEATS
.Nm
is not a job queue, scheduler, retry daemon, pub/sub system, lock manager,
workflow engine, or per-event delivery mechanism.
It is only a named, coalescing, edge-triggered runner.
No event payloads are passed to the command; the command reconciles against
durable external state.
